text:
23:45 for anyone curious, they'd use a gas or coal fuelled water heater to... heat water, and then pour it into a bathtub using buckets or pans.

In the old west, most people sponge bathed daily rather than submerged themselves in a tub, but when they did use a tub, they bathed in cold water. They would often share used bath water (among the family, and even in public bath houses... yuck), hot baths were considered a luxury, since heating enough water to fill a tub took time and hauling the water to the tub took effort. Meanwhile, at public baths, like the one in this game, a bath with hot, unused water would be considered expensive, with soap also costing extra. 

I'm sure this is a part of the old west Gura would not be fond of.

text:
Imagine this scene, if you will:
It's the 1700s, everything is tough, and making a few bucks is downright heavenly.
